Sentencas: This paper presents a multiphysical model for a microtubular solid-oxide fuel cell (SOFC) using syngas as fuel.
Titulo: Co-Oxidation Modeling for a Syngas-Supplied Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The proposed control-oriented syngas fuel cell model includes both hydrogen and carbon monoxide co-oxidation phenomena and is demonstrated through the electrochemical, fluidic, and thermal dynamic characteristics of the fuel cell.
Titulo: Co-Oxidation Modeling for a Syngas-Supplied Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The developed model is validated experimentally under different operating conditions regarding different reaction temperatures, species partial pressures, and entire working range of current densities.
Titulo: Co-Oxidation Modeling for a Syngas-Supplied Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: As an important part of the model, the co-oxidation phenomenon of hydrogen and carbon monoxide is discussed in details.
Titulo: Co-Oxidation Modeling for a Syngas-Supplied Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The developed model can be used in embedded applications such as real-time simulation, which can help to design and test the control and online diagnostic strategy for fuel cell power generation system in the industrial applications.
Titulo: Co-Oxidation Modeling for a Syngas-Supplied Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cell
